b'[<p><i><b>UFC 71: Liddell vs. Jackson 2</b></i> was a <a href="/wiki/Mixed_martial_arts" title="Mixed martial arts">mixed martial arts</a> event held by the <a href="/wiki/Ultimate_Fighting_Championship" title="Ultimate Fighting Championship">Ultimate Fighting Championship</a>. The event took place on Saturday, May 26, 2007 at the <a href="/wiki/MGM_Grand_Garden_Arena" title="MGM Grand Garden Arena">MGM Grand Garden Arena</a> in <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Las_Vegas,_Nevada" title="Las Vegas, Nevada">Las Vegas, Nevada</a>.\n</p>, <p>The main event was the rematch between UFC Light Heavyweight Champion <a href="/wiki/Chuck_Liddell" title="Chuck Liddell">Chuck Liddell</a> and <a href="/wiki/Quinton_Jackson" title="Quinton Jackson">Quinton "Rampage" Jackson</a>. At the time of the event, Jackson was the only fighter to have an unavenged victory over Liddell, which occurred at <i><a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/PRIDE_Final_Conflict_2003" title="PRIDE Final Conflict 2003">PRIDE Final Conflict 2003</a></i> by TKO.\n</p>, <p>The UFC announced during the broadcast of the card that the winner of the Jackson vs.  Liddell bout will face PRIDE 93\xc2\xa0kg and 83\xc2\xa0kg Champion <a href="/wiki/Dan_Henderson" title="Dan Henderson">Dan Henderson</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-doyle_1-2"><a href="#cite_note-doyle-1">[1]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>Mainstream sports media, especially <a href="/wiki/ESPN" title="ESPN">ESPN</a>, began extensive coverage of the UFC on this event. ESPN broadcast live the weigh-ins and post-fight coverage for <i>UFC 71</i> on <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/ESPNEWS" title="ESPNEWS">ESPNEWS</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-3"><a href="#cite_note-3">[3]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><a href="/wiki/Alan_Belcher" title="Alan Belcher">Alan Belcher</a> replaced <a href="/wiki/Eric_Schafer" title="Eric Schafer">Eric Schafer</a> for his fight against <a href="/wiki/Sean_Salmon" title="Sean Salmon">Sean Salmon</a> due to an injury.\n</p>, <p><br/>\n</p>, <p>After every UFC event, bonuses are given to fighters who perform well.\n</p>, <p>The bonuses for this event were $40,000 each.\n</p>]'